I hit this as well.   The action works from the command line.   The action expects one parameter stocklist with a value of {"stocks":[{"symbol":"IBM"},{"symbol":"MSFT"}]}  
``` 
ibmcloud fn action invoke helloworld  -r
Plug-in 'cloud-functions 1.0.47' is now available (you have 1.0.44).
Use 'ibmcloud plugin update cloud-functions' to upgrade the plug-in.
Use 'ibmcloud config --check-version=false' to disable update check.

{
    "stocklist": {
        "stocks": [
            {
                "symbol": "IBM"
            },
            {
                "symbol": "MSFT"
            }
        ]
    }
}
```
When I try to run the postman using the url I get an error. 
<img width="1447" alt="Screenshot 2020-10-18 at 19 26 57" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60844296/96376610-e5da4700-1177-11eb-9346-aa7f168e41dc.png">

A quick experiment using couch indexing suggests linking the trigger to the rule would achieve the desired result.

```
function (doc) {
  var PATHSEP = "/";
  var isRule = function (doc) {  return (doc.trigger !== undefined) };
  if (isRule(doc)) try {
    var ns = doc.namespace.split(PATHSEP);
    var root = ns[0];
    var v = {_id: doc.trigger.path + PATHSEP + doc.trigger.name };
    emit([doc.namespace, doc.updated], v);
    if (root !== doc.namespace) {
      emit([root, doc.updated], 1);
    }
  } catch (e) {}
}
```

